experiences some extremes of heat in summer and cold in winter, but except in the himalayan regions, snow is almost unheard of. november to january is the winter season and april and may are the hot months when everyone eagerly awaits the rains. there is also a brief spring in february and march, especially in north india. opinions are divided on whether any part of india actually experiences an autumn, but the ancients had certainly identified such a season among the six seasons ( or ritus - vasanta - spring, greeshma - summer, varsha - rainy, sharat - autumn, shishira 